# Quick Start

### Clone
```
git clone https://github.com/ShaneJ-Ai/Factorise-Technologies.git
cd Factorise-Technologies
```
# Contributing Guide

## 1) Core rules (production-grade)

### Protected branches
- `main` and `develop` are protected.
- Direct pushes are blocked (PRs only).
- Required checks before merge:
  - CI must pass (lint/test/build)
  - Required approvals (team setting; recommended: 1â€“2)
  - Branch must be up-to-date with the target branch
- Force-push disabled on protected branches.

### Stability expectations
- `main` is always production-ready.
- `develop` is integration-ready (staging-ready). It may change frequently, but must not be broken.

---

## 2) Branch model 

### Branches
- `main`: production
- `develop`: integration / staging
- `feature/<short-desc>`: new functionality
- `bugfix/<short-desc>`: non-urgent fixes
- `release/<yyyy-mm-dd>` or `release/<version>`: stabilization for an upcoming prod release
- `hotfix/<short-desc>`: urgent production fixes from `main`

### Naming 
- `feature/users-crud`
- `bugfix/fix-validation-message`
- `release/2026-01-15`
- `hotfix/fix-login-500`

---

## 3) Standard workflow (feature/bugfix â†’ develop)

### A) Start from latest develop
```bash
git checkout develop
git pull origin develop
```

## 2. Create a Feature Branch
```
git checkout -b feature/<short-name>
```
## 3. Work & Commit
```
git add -A
git commit -m "feat: short, clear description"

```


# ðŸ§¼ Clean Git Workflow (Rebase)

This project always uses rebase to keep history clean and readable.

## Sync main
```
git checkout main
git pull --rebase origin main
```
## Rebase Your Branch (Before PR)
```
git fetch origin
git rebase origin/main
```
## If Conflicts Occur
```
git status
```
# fix conflicts
```
git add -A
git rebase --continue
```
## Abort If Needed
```
git rebase --abort
```


# ðŸ“¤ Push Your Branch
```
git push -u origin feature/<short-name>
```
## Push Rejected? (Branch Behind)
```
git pull --rebase origin main
git push
```



# ðŸš¨ Hard Reset 

## Force local branch to match remote:
```
git fetch origin
git reset --hard origin/main
git clean -fd
```

